# Hook — Playwright skill

When creating or editing files that match the **globs** above, **read first** (Read tool) the skill entry point:

- **`.agents/skills/playwright-skill/SKILL.md`** — Golden Rules + guide index.

Then open **only** guides relevant to the task under **`.agents/skills/playwright-skill/core/`** (or `playwright-cli/` for terminal automation), for example:

| Task | File |
|------|------|
| Locators | `core/locator-strategy.md` |
| Assertions / waiting | `core/assertions-and-waiting.md` |
| Structure / naming | `core/test-organization.md` |
| Fixtures / hooks | `core/fixtures-and-hooks.md` |
| Test data | `core/test-data-management.md` |
| Login / auth | `core/authentication.md` |

**Short reminders from SKILL:** prefer `getByRole`; use `getByTestId` when `data-test(id)` hooks are an intentional UI contract; **web-first** `expect(locator)`; no `waitForTimeout`; keep `baseURL` in config/fixture and avoid repeating absolute URLs in specs; shared setup via **fixtures** (`test.extend`).

Do not add patterns the skill explicitly avoids (for example asserting on raw `textContent()`) without a strong, brief justification.
